{"schema_version":"1.7.3","id":"OESA-2025-1281","published":"2025-03-14T15:44:20Z","modified":"2025-09-03T06:30:59.241750Z","upstream":["CVE-2020-24370"],"summary":"syslinux security update","details":"The Syslinux Project covers lightweight bootloaders for MS-DOS FAT filesystems (SYSLINUX), network booting (PXELINUX), bootable &amp;quot;El Torito&amp;quot; CD-ROMs (ISOLINUX), and Linux ext2/ext3/ext4 or btrfs filesystems (EXTLINUX). The project also includes MEMDISK, a tool to boot legacy operating systems (such as DOS) from nontraditional media; it is usually used in conjunction with PXELINUX and ISOLINUX.\r\n\r\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\nldebug.c in Lua 5.4.0 allows a negation overflow and segmentation fault in getlocal and setlocal, as demonstrated by getlocal(3,2^31).(CVE-2020-24370)","affected":[{"package":{"name":"syslinux","ecosystem":"openEuler:24.03-LTS-SP1","purl":"pkg:rpm/openEuler/syslinux&distro=openEuler-24.03-LTS-SP1"},"ranges":[{"type":"ECOSYSTEM","events":[{"introduced":"0"},{"fixed":"6.04-17.oe2403sp1"}]}],"ecosystem_specific":{"noarch":["syslinux-extlinux-nonlinux-6.04-17.oe2403sp1.noarch.rpm","syslinux-nonlinux-6.04-17.oe2403sp1.noarch.rpm","syslinux-tftpboot-6.04-17.oe2403sp1.noarch.rpm"],"src":["syslinux-6.04-17.oe2403sp1.src.rpm"],"x86_64":["syslinux-6.04-17.oe2403sp1.x86_64.rpm","syslinux-debuginfo-6.04-17.oe2403sp1.x86_64.rpm","syslinux-debugsource-6.04-17.oe2403sp1.x86_64.rpm","syslinux-devel-6.04-17.oe2403sp1.x86_64.rpm","syslinux-efi64-6.04-17.oe2403sp1.x86_64.rpm","syslinux-extlinux-6.04-17.oe2403sp1.x86_64.rpm","syslinux-perl-6.04-17.oe2403sp1.x86_64.rpm"]},"database_specific":{"source":"https://repo.openeuler.org/security/data/osv/OESA-2025-1281.json"}}],"references":[{"type":"ADVISORY","url":"https://www.openeuler.org/zh/security/security-bulletins/detail/?id=openEuler-SA-2025-1281"},{"type":"ADVISORY","url":"https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2020-24370"}],"database_specific":{"severity":"Medium"}}